This video is exactly what the title says, but it is about therapeutic massage, not sensual massage. It gives a good introduction to what therapeutic massage is, how it is done, and why it is done, including Swedish massage, aromatherapy, reflexology, remedial massage, and sports massage. If you are thinking about getting a massage for the first time, this will give you a solid idea of what to expect from a trained professional. If you are considering becoming a masseur, this will give you a good introduction to what you will do if you pursue this career. Watching this video should allow you to make an informed choice as to whether or not to get a massage or to become a masseuse.

As it says in other reviews, the masseurs in this video are older, but that means they have a lot of experience and understanding, which makes their narration all the better. They do speak with an Australian accent, but it is not too heavy for me to understand and I'm originally from Georgia (USA). The production quality is not Hollywood, but it good enough for the viewer to clearly see and hear what they are doing.

If you are looking for a slick production or sexy or soft-porn video, this is not it. If you are looking for a video that will show you what a professional massage is like and how it works, this does it well.

Its quite outdated and to be very frank ...boring.  I do not care that the therapists are old at all, but there should really be a camera person to get up close to the areas the therapist is working and not just a stationary tri-pod.  More layman terms used and a little more emotion and focus on each movement.  I've been doing body work for over 30 yrs so I know what and why the Therapists are doing but for someone that is new and wants to learn it looks just like rubbing.  This may not be the video for instruction that you are looking for.
